NAME
  cp - copy files and directory

SYNOPSIS
  cp [OPTION] SOURCES TARGET

DESCRIPTION
  Copy files or directory in SOURCES  to TARGET.
  If SOURCES is ONE file or directory, it will be copied as the file(DIRECTORY) named TARGET. 
  If SOURCES is several files and directories, it will be copied into the direcotry named TARGET.

  -r 
    it means the following arguments includes directory. Without this option, you cannot copy a directory.
  
  

